tiaraConfigMgmtMib.name: tiaraConfigMgmtMib

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tiaraConfigMgmtMib.contactinfo: Tiara Networks Customer Service 525 Race Street, Suite 100, San Jose, CA 95126 USA Tel: +1 408-216-4700 Fax: +1 408-216-4701 Email: support@tiaranetworks.com
tiaraConfigMgmtMib.description: Configuration management MIB. This MIB represents a model of configuration data that exists in various locations: current In use by the running system. local Saved locally in NVRAM or flash. remote Saved to some server on the network. The purpose of this MIB is to track changes and saves of the current configuration.

cfgNetOperTable.name: cfgNetOperTable
cfgNetOperTable.description: A table of configuration from network operation entries. Each entry represents a separate operation to configure the system from a file located on a server on the network. The management station should create an entry with a random number as an index to perform the operation. The management station should then retrieve the entry with the same random number as an index and examine the value of the cfgNetOperStatus variable to get the status of the operation.

cfgNetOperEntry.name: cfgNetOperEntry
cfgNetOperEntry.description: Entry to initiate an operation. Each entry consists of a command and required parameters. Once the operation completes, the management station should retrieve the value of the status object and delete the entry from the table.

cfgNetOperRandomNumber.name: cfgNetOperRandomNumber
cfgNetOperRandomNumber.description: Object specifying a unique entry in the table. A management station wishing to initiate a configuration operation should use a pseudo-random value for this object when creating a cfgNetOperEntry.

cfgNetOperCommand.name: cfgNetOperCommand
cfgNetOperCommand.description: The commands to be executed configure from the network or save the configuration to the network. Command Remarks. config Configure from network. save Save configuration to network.

cfgNetOperAddress.name: cfgNetOperAddress
cfgNetOperAddress.description: The Internet address of the server.

cfgNetOperFileName.name: cfgNetOperFileName
cfgNetOperFileName.description: The destination or source file name on the network server.

cfgNetOperStatus.name: cfgNetOperStatus
cfgNetOperStatus.description: Represents the status of the operation. If the operation has not started or an operation is not being performed, then the value of this object would be idle(0).

cfgFlashOperTable.name: cfgFlashOperTable
cfgFlashOperTable.description: A table of config/save from/to flash operation entries. Each entry represents a separate operation to configure the system from a file located on a local flash-file system. The management station should create an entry with a random number as an index to perform the operation. The management station should then retrive the entry with the same random number as an index and examine the value of the cfgFlashOperStatus variable to get the status of the operation.

cfgFlashOperEntry.name: cfgFlashOperEntry
cfgFlashOperEntry.description: Entry to initiate an operation. Each entry consists of a command and required parameters. Once the operation completes, the management station should retrieve the value of the status object and delete the entry from the table.

cfgFlashOperRandomNumber.name: cfgFlashOperRandomNumber
cfgFlashOperRandomNumber.description: Object specifying a unique entry in the table. A management station wishing to initiate a configuration operation should use a pseudo-random value for this object when creating a cfgFlashOperEntry.

cfgFlashOperCommand.name: cfgFlashOperCommand
cfgFlashOperCommand.description: The commands to be executed configure from the network or save the configuration to the network. Command Remarks. config Config from network. save Save the configuration to the network.

cfgFlashOperFileName.name: cfgFlashOperFileName
cfgFlashOperFileName.description: The destination or source file name on the network server.

cfgFlashOperStatus.name: cfgFlashOperStatus
cfgFlashOperStatus.description: The status of the operation. If the operation has not started or an operation is not being performed, then the value of this object would be idle(0).

CfgMedium.name: CfgMedium
CfgMedium.description: The source or destination of a configuration change, save, or copy. commandSource The source of the command. current Live operational data from RAM. flash Local flash. network Network host.

cfgCurrentLastChanged.name: cfgCurrentLastChanged
cfgCurrentLastChanged.description: The last time the current configuration was changed.

cfgCurrentLastSaved.name: cfgCurrentLastSaved
cfgCurrentLastSaved.description: The last time the current configuration was saved.

cfgMaxEvents.name: cfgMaxEvents
cfgMaxEvents.description: The maximum number of entries that can be held in the cfgEventTable. The system stores the 20 most recent history events in a circular style. These events are also saved to flash. Up to the last 10 entries can be saved if space is available in flash.

cfgEventTable.name: cfgEventTable
cfgEventTable.description: A table of configuration history events.

cfgEventEntry.name: cfgEventEntry
cfgEventEntry.description: Entry holding information about a configuration event.

cfgEventIndex.name: cfgEventIndex
cfgEventIndex.description: Index in the history event table.

cfgEventTime.name: cfgEventTime
cfgEventTime.description: The time when the configuration occurred.

cfgEventConfigProtocol.name: cfgEventConfigProtocol
cfgEventConfigProtocol.description: The source of the command that resulted in the event.

cfgEventConfigSrc.name: cfgEventConfigSrc
cfgEventConfigSrc.description: The configuration data source for the event.

cfgEventConfigDst.name: cfgEventConfigDst
cfgEventConfigDst.description: The configuration data destination for the event.

cfgEventLoginType.name: cfgEventLoginType
cfgEventLoginType.description: Configuration via telnet or rlogin, etc.

cfgEventTerminalUser.name: cfgEventTerminalUser
cfgEventTerminalUser.description: This object represents the logged in user name if configuration is via the CLI. It represents the community name if configuration is via SNMP. Otherwise, the object string length is zero if not available or not applicable.

cfgEventConfigSrcAddress.name: cfgEventConfigSrcAddress
cfgEventConfigSrcAddress.description: The Internet address of the connected system. The value is 0.0.0.0 if not available or not applicable.

cfgEventFileName.name: cfgEventFileName
cfgEventFileName.description: If the system is set for configuration via a network, then this object represents the file name on some server.

cfgEnableChangeNotification.name: cfgEnableChangeNotification
cfgEnableChangeNotification.description: Indicates whether the system produces the cfgChangeNotification. The default is yes.

cfgEnableSaveNotification.name: cfgEnableSaveNotification
cfgEnableSaveNotification.description: Indicates whether the system produces the cfgSaveNotification. The default is yes.

cfgEventChangeNotification.name: cfgEventChangeNotification
cfgEventChangeNotification.description: Send the configuration change event via either trap or info request PDU

cfgEventSaveNotification.name: cfgEventSaveNotification
cfgEventSaveNotification.description: Send the configuration save event via either trap or info request PDU
